This paper is likely to belong to the Natural Language Processing (NLP) and Computer Vision (CV) sub-fields of Computer Science. The paper describes the creation of two new datasets with images described by humans, which involves both NLP and CV techniques. The use of Amazon Mechanical Turk, a crowdsourcing platform, also suggests a Human-Computer Interaction (HCI) aspect to the research, which falls under the cs.HC sub-category. Additionally, the paper involves information retrieval (IR) techniques in analyzing the properties of the datasets. Finally, the use of clipart objects in one of the datasets suggests a Multimedia (MM) aspect to the research.
